[start section id="20103"]

Mr. Peloquin with a long-standing history of Crohn's disease and history of chronic peri-rectal abscesses with multiple drainage and Malecot Drain placements. On 5/13/2010 MRI showed a large left perirectal horseshoe-shaped abscess with associated lower anal fistulous tracts.  Sigmoidoscopy performed on 5/14/2010 showed a low-grade mucinous adenocarcinoma from the peri-rectal region. Therefore the patient is scheduled for an Abdominal Perineal Resection on 9/8/2010. He has completed chemoradiation on July 16, 2010.

